cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CC

This paper discusses the cognitive limits of human beings in recognizing syntactic structures in Japanese and English sentences. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also uses statistical analysis to support its findings, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses cognitive psychology, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
